   and described for the first time: the male of P. (H.) frontalis
   Timberlake, 1968, the female of P. (H.) optiva Timberlake, 1954, and the
   true male of P. (H.) pilonotata Timberlake, 1980. Perdita (H.)
   fasciatella Timberlake, 1980 is proposed as a junior synonym of P. (H.)
