Month = {{AUG}},
Abstract = {{Insects provide ecosystem services, such as pollination and biological
   control. Additionally, flowering ornamental plant species have the
   potential to support beneficial insect communities, such as pollinating
   bees, wasps, and predatory plant bugs. We conducted visual observations
   and sampled via sweep nets to assess the potential of flowering
   ornamentals to act as a conservation resource for pollinators.
